# AI Execution, Safety & Token-Optimized Protocols (CRITICAL)

## 0. AUTONOMOUS EXECUTION & HEALING
- **No Permission Needed:** Execute commands, code fixes, and server restarts autonomously, EXCEPT for Rule 7 gates. Do NOT ask for "Run" or "Accept" confirmations.
- **Zero Error Tolerance:** Check browser/server logs after every change. Fix red/yellow errors autonomously immediately.
- **Manual Orchestrator:** Do NOT run `orchestrator.py` in the background. When the user runs it manually and reports an error, autonomously apply fixes.

## 1. STRICT TOKEN CONSERVATION & SNIPPET-ONLY OUTPUT (CRITICAL)
- **Zero Full-File Output:** NEVER output entire files unless explicitly requested by the user. 
- **Snippet Focus:** ONLY output the specific functions, methods, or code blocks being modified. Use placeholders (`// ... existing code ...`) for unchanged parts to aggressively save output tokens.
- **Concise Responses:** Keep all text explanations, code summaries, and debug logs extremely brief and direct.

## 2. WORKSPACE & ENVIRONMENT RESTRICTIONS
- **Manual Git Only:** NO automatic `git` commands. Only commit/push when requested, using origin `https://github.com/ahmedalyzidan/TED-Capital-ERP`.
- **Workspace:** Path is `C:\Users\Ahmed Zidan\ERP\backend\Ted ERP\backend`. 
- **Dev Environment:** 
  - Backend uses `npm start`. Frontend uses `npm run dev` (NEVER open port 5173 manually).
  - AI Proxy runs `qwen2.5-coder:32b` via LiteLLM on Port `4040`.

## 3. DEFENSIVE UI & SCHEMA INTEGRITY
- **Defensive Rendering:** MUST use optional chaining (`?.`) and fallbacks (`|| 'Default'`) in frontend components to prevent runtime crashes.
- **Schema First:** Verify SQL tables in `schemaFixes.js` before adding modules. 
- **Zero Console Errors:** Clear all red console errors immediately after any UI/Backend update.

## 4. GATED CLOUD DEPLOYMENT (STRICT)
- **Zero Autonomous Cloud Action:** Follow this manual gate strictly. All changes remain local until Phase 2.
  1. **Local:** Code and verify locally.
  2. **Staging Gate:** Ask: *"Verified locally. Push to Staging?"* -> If Yes: push to Git & run `bash deploy-staging.sh`.
  3. **Prod Gate:** Ask: *"Staging updated. Deploy to Production?"* -> If Yes: run `bash update-erp.sh`.
- Output state: *"Workflow Status: [LOCAL/STAGING/PRODUCTION] - Awaiting Approval."*

## 5. CONTEXT & TESTING PROTOCOL
- **Context:** Rely on `project_context.txt` (user will manually update it).
- **Financial Logic:** Do not push financial changes without manual `pytest -m finance` success confirmation from the user.
- **Startup:** Prioritize using `start_erp_dev.bat` for initializing services cleanly.

