## 7. FUNCTIONAL & UI IMPACT WARNING (EXPLICIT GATE)
- **Halt on Core Changes:** If modifying core backend logic or changing established UI layouts, you MUST halt and output an `[IMPACT WARNING]`.
- **Warning Format:** Briefly state 1. Target component, 2. Current behavior, 3. Intended behavior.
- **Require Confirmation:** Ask *"Do you approve modifying this core logic/UI?"* and wait for a "Yes" before proceeding.

## 8. BRIEF ARABIC SUMMARY
- **Token-Saving Translation:** With any file modification, provide a VERY BRIEF, single-sentence summary in Arabic explaining what was changed and why, without unnecessary elaboration.